race.comment: Terrific race. Plenty of well-performed gallopers resuming but with the one run under the belt TWAIN'S ANGEL (10) looks set to run well. Just missed the frame in the rich Kalgoorlie Golden Saddle when fresh and has a strong second-up record. Should be in the finish. LONDON'S IMAGE (11) hasn't raced since tackling tougher grade at Flemington in the autumn. Has a terrific record this level and is drawn to take catching with the in-form Fiore aboard. SUPER SMINK (9) is another coming back from an autumn campaign in Melbourne, the latest in the Group 1 Futurity. Well placed this level and goes close on best form. ROPE THEM IN (2) resumes and does boast an excellent fresh-up record. Drawn for a soft run and will be hard to hold out late. AZTEC RULER (4) is another who can run a big race fresh and will be spotting a start but winding up late.
